  "texts": [
    "In fact, fingerprints generally provide satisfactory performance for quantitative structureactivity relationship (QSAR) modeling [8][9][10], even in the presence of activity cliffs [11].",
    "Given the relevance of fingerprints in cheminformatics, over 30 years of research in the field have led to a broad and diverse selection of fingerprinting algorithms [12,13].",
    "However, while extensive research exists on the performance of these algorithms on synthetic, drug-like molecules, little is known about the best practices for natural products encoding.Stemming from these observations, the aim of this study is to comprehensively compare and evaluate how different types of molecular fingerprints perform for modeling the NP chemical space, and ultimately to (a) provide effective recommendations to cheminformatics practitioners in the field of NPs, and (b) underscore future directions for the development of molecular fingerprints.",
    "We systematically compared 20 different molecular fingerprinting algorithms from four packages [14][15][16][17][18], on two cheminformatics tasks.",
    "First, we evaluate the similarity of fingerprints encoding using the COCO-NUT database [4], containing over 400,000 unique NPs from 52 different sources, and a wide variety of organisms, geographic locations and applications."
